                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-322-off1722 t18260406-322-victim1718"></join>
                  </persName>
             and others, his partners.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-322-person1719">
                  CHARLES 
                  TOWNSEND
               <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1719" type="surname" value="TOWNSEND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1719" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1719" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am warehouseman to Thomas Conway and others - they are wholesale grocers and tea dealers, and live in Maiden-lane, Queen-street, City. On Thursday last, the 6th of April, I loaded the cart with one chest of tea, one bag of tea, and some sugars; I gave it in charge of Blunt, the carman, about half-past eleven o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-322-person1720">
                  JOSEPH 
                  BLUNT
               <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1720" type="surname" value="BLUNT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1720" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1720" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the carman. I received this chest of tea in my cart on Thursday last; I drove it along Bishopsgate-street, and there I stopped; I was about forty yards behind the cart when I saw the prisoner go and move the chest of tea from the side to the tail - he then turned round and lifted it over the chain, took it on his shoulder, and walked away; I ran and caught him about half-way across the road.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-322-person1721">
                  THOMAS 
                  WHITFIELD
               <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1721" type="surname" value="WHITFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1721" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1721" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent down to Liverpool-street; I met the carman, who called and asked me to have something to drink - we were going to have it, when he turned round and said "I have a chest of tea in my cart, and I must have a sharp eye on it;" he then saw the prisoner taken it and ran after him; I saw him drop the chest, which Blunt gave me charge of, and he took the prisoner - the chest was close at his heels.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-322-person1722">
                  WILLIAM 
                  RILEY
               <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1722" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1722" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-322-person1722" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner and the tea.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going along Bishopsgate-street, and a man asked me if I wanted a job; I said Yes; he said "If you will take this chest of tea to the Catherine Wheel, I will pay for it."</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18260406-322-verdict1724" type="verdictDescription">
